": "text", "text": ": (S, O, and so in the CK:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he cut it in pieces;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaT~aEahu", "text_ar": "قَطَّعَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (So in several copies of the K and in the TA.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "grbl", "text_ar": "غربل"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alqawoma", "text_ar": "القَوْمَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He slew,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "crushed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ground"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the people,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "company of men."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) Hence the saying, in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kayofa bikumo A_i*aA kunotumo fiY zamaAnK", "text_ar": "كَيْفَ بِكُمْ اـِذَا كُنْتُمْ فِى زَمَانٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yugarobalu Aln~aAsu fiyhi", "text_ar": "يُغَرْبَلُ النَّاسُ فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, * TA) i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "will it be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with you when ye shall be in a time when men"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "shall be slain,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "crushed?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when the best of them shall be taken away and the worst of them shall remain;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like as is done by the sifter of wheat? (O, TA:) or, in the opinion of Suh, as he says in the R,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when they shall be searched to the utmost, and pursued one after another?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "agreeably with the saying of Mek- hool Ed-Dimashkee,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daxalotu Al$~aA^oma fagarobalotuhaA garobalapF", "text_ar": "دَخَلْتُ الشَّاْمَ فَغَرْبَلْتُهَا غَرْبَلَةً"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hat~aY lamo A^adaEo EilomFA A_il~aA Hawayotuhu", "text_ar": "حَتَّى لَمْ اَدَعْ عِلْمًا اـِلَّا حَوَيْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I entered Syria, and searched it to the utmost in such a manner that I left not a science but I acquired it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gurobila Alqatiylu", "text_ar": "غُرْبِلَ القَتِيلُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The slain man became swollen,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "inflated, and raised his legs."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "MA", "O", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}